                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Charter</title>
                     
                     
                     
                     <title xml:lang="he"/>
                     
                     
                     
                     <note>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Grant by William the son of Roger de Castre to Newhouse Abbey (Co. Lincoln) of a  messuage late belonging to Arn Thol in the town of Castre [Caistor, co. Lincoln], at a yearly rent of 8d, the Abbey acquitting the grantor of £10 due by him to the Jews. A.D. 1232. Amonf the witnesses are: Ralph de Rowelle, Dean of Newhouse, and William de Silvedune.  </p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>For related Hebrew charter (the acquittance to the grantor of debts and the release of the messuage), see Harley Ch 43 A 60 B.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        <p>Inscription on the seal: 'Sigill. Wilelm fili Roger'? (hardly legible).</p>
                     
                     
                     
                     </note>
                  
                  
                  
